org.mybatis.generator.plugins.annotations

Class JaxbAnnotations

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.mybatis.generator.api.PluginAdapter
      • org.mybatis.generator.plugins.annotations.JaxbAnnotations
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.mybatis.generator.api.Plugin
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    FieldTypeJaxbAnnotations, PropertyTypeJaxbAnnotations

    public abstract class JaxbAnnotations
extends org.mybatis.generator.api.PluginAdapter
    JaxbAnnotations is the abstract base class for plugins that add JAXB Annotation support for XML marshalling and unmarshalling of the generated model classes. This class defines most of the methods that subclasses will call for the actual insertion of the JAXB annotations into the generated model classes.

    The only abstract method in this class is: public abstract String getXmlAccessTypeConstant, which returns a String indicating the JAXB XMLAccessType that will be used to annotate the generated model classes.
    Subclasses must override this method to return one of the supported JAXB XMLAccessTypes, such as XmlAccessType.FIELD, XmlAccessType.PUBLIC_MEMBER, etc.

    For example, a subclass can specify that the generated model class will be annotated with type XmlAccessType.FIELD, by overriding the getXmlAccessTypeConstant method to return the String: "@XmlAccessorType(XmlAccessType.FIELD)"

    This class does not support the marshalling and unmarshalling of the auto generated Example Classes, which are also generated along with other model classes. Unlike the other auto generated model classes, Example classes are not a "Domain Object" (or "DTO") type of class and so the marshalling and unmarshalling of these classes should not be needed. Subclasses are however free to add support for marshalling and unmarshalling of the Example Classes, if they so choose.

        public abstract java.lang.String getXmlAccessTypeConstant()

        Subclasses must override this method to return one of the supported JAXB XMLAccessTypes, such as XmlAccessType.FIELD, XmlAccessType.PUBLIC_MEMBER, etc.
